          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-12-23T14:47:15Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Ensuring Quality Care for our Veterans Act</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to contract with a nonfederal organization to conduct a quality management review of hospital care or medical services furnished by each Veterans Health Administration (VHA) provider whose license was terminated by a state licensing board based upon care or services provided in a non-VHA facility.</p> <p>If a review determines that the standard of care was not met, the VA shall notify the individual who received such care or services.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-10-24T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
